			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Hi Maurine,</p>
<p>Yes, you&#8217;d put the width on the #navbar element. The width you choose is entirely up to you&#8230; it should be exactly as wide as you want your entire navigation bar (links + background) to be. So if your site is 800px wide, choose 800px. After that, Richard is right: a margin of &#8220;auto&#8221; on the left and right sides will center your element.</p>
