			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Hi (other) RobG,</p>
<p>Generally speaking, if the submenu disappears before your mouse can get to it, that suggests you have a margin between your main list item and your submenu. You might need to write a more agressive &#8220;margin: 0&#8243; rule on all of your navigation uls and lis to account for a conflicting rule somewhere else in your site&#8217;s stylesheet.</p>
<p>The brass tacks: hover works on padding, but does not on margin. You can use padding to create space. Margin is right out.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

			
